WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.977
The adverse effects of myocarditis span a

00:00:02.977 --> 00:00:03.828
critical spectrum.

00:00:03.828 --> 00:00:06.805
Acute heart failure affects up to 25

00:00:06.805 --> 00:00:09.782
percent of patients, with progression to end-stage

00:00:09.782 --> 00:00:12.759
heart failure in 12 to 25 percent.

00:00:12.759 --> 00:00:15.736
Ventricular arrhythmias — including sustained ventricular tachycardia

00:00:15.736 --> 00:00:18.287
— carry significant sudden death risk.

00:00:18.287 --> 00:00:21.264
Cardiogenic shock occurs in fulminant presentations, with

00:00:21.264 --> 00:00:24.241
giant cell myocarditis carrying a 62 percent

00:00:24.241 --> 00:00:27.218
rate of death or transplant at 60

00:00:27.218 --> 00:00:27.644
days.

00:00:27.644 --> 00:00:30.621
Chronic dilated cardiomyopathy develops in a subset

00:00:30.621 --> 00:00:31.897
following apparent recovery.

00:00:31.897 --> 00:00:34.874
Complete heart block requiring pacing can complicate

00:00:34.874 --> 00:00:37.000
sarcoid and giant cell variants.
